<img src=http://www.inficad.com/~daltonm/sigpics/ickhorsig.jpg>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utinyntinagyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tinyn Tinagyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 292<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/17/01 4:58:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How much does taunt &quot;taunt&quot; ?</span><hr size=1> When Taunt is pressed, there is a check against how high the players skill is in Taunt. If the check succeds, the taunter is bumped to the top of the agro list, no matter how much agro is needed to get him there. If it fails, he stays where he is. Also heard that you can not successfully taunt mobs that are higher level then you, unless you are L60, then you can possibly taunt mobs up to L65. <p><font size="-1">Tinyn Tinagyn - Yellow and Green Troubador of the 56th Song, on Brell Serilis<br>
Sometimes, when you throw men down hard enough, they bounce.</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uickhorvonmemnoch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ickhor Von Memnoch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gnomosexual</span><br>  Posts: 413<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/17/01 8:30:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How much does taunt &quot;taunt&quot; ?</span><hr size=1> But how far on top of the aggro list am i?<br>
