<a href=http://pub57.ezboard.com/baachoardail>[Future DAoC player]<i>*board mod*</i></a>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrungleeisenguss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krungle Eisenguss</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/18/01 1:32:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How much does taunt &quot;taunt&quot; ?</span><hr size=1> I have found that doing something to increase your standing on the Hate List right before taunt increases the chance of a successful Taunt. As a palli I use Flash of Light (used to, no room now most of the time for the spell) and/or Stun then hit taunt the second the spell lands. Works almost everytime. Root is even a greater taunter, but not recomended when there is someone Snaring. I have heard Warriors will Beg right before Taunt to increase their chances of a successful Taunt.<br>
<br>
As far as taunting something over your level, it can and has been done by me. It is alot harder to do but I do it. I have done it since my High Keep days. The trick is, again, to piss them off with a spell first then taunt the second the spell lands.<br>
<br>
Krungle Eisenguss<br>
Grand Master Taunter<br>
Casters' Comrad <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglesig.jpg" border=0></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvumil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vumil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Administrator <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle><br><font color=#A0B0E0>&lt;<a href=http://www.silentredemption.org>Silent Redemption</a>&gt;  </font></span><br>  Posts: 1253<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/18/01 2:12:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How much does taunt &quot;taunt&quot; ?</span><hr size=1> You can only taunt mobs which are your level or lower.. unless you are level 60, then you can taunt mobs up to level 65. <p><br><font face="Arial" size="-2">Vumil Darksoul (retired)<br>
Kendon 
<br>
ICQ #: 33693268
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubeatrixmaledicta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beatrix Maledicta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle></span><br>  Posts: 148<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/20/01 5:15:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How much does taunt &quot;taunt&quot; ?</span><hr size=1> I feel there's a lot of speculation around taunt. That's why tanks get almost superstitious when it comes to taunting and our ways to improve taunt. I for one would like to see the exact formula - exactly what parameters are included - before drawing final conclusions. But I can tell you for sure that my lucky rabbit's foot from Velious has helped me a lot in taunting. Get one!<br>
 <p><b>Beatrix Maledicta</b><br>
Warrioress, barbarian, size 54<br>
Europa Tribes<br>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uarathena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arathena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dark Valkyrie of Innoruuk</span><br>  Posts: 399<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/20/01 7:29:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How much does taunt &quot;taunt&quot; ?</span><hr size=1> Well, taunt will shoot you up to the very top of the hate list, that much is more or less agreed upon. The margin by which it does so, however, is debateable, but I prefer to consider it much like Ichor has said: 1 point. However, every single taunting tank (Warrior, paladin, SK, and ranger) has the ability to deliberately choose to dish out damage immediately after the taunt, that is, through timing, kicking, bashing or casting.  It's also likely that you're more likely to succeed if you're farther up the hate list to begin with, or at least it makes a ton of sense, which would produce Krungle's(Did I spell that right? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) observations, as Stun is a relatively high taunt in conjunction with melee damage. <br>
Personally, for taunting purposes, I will usually layer up my DoTs, then chain cast Shadow Vortex while pounding taunt/bash every time bash cycles... It seems to work fairly well, or at least, nothing ever goes after our enchanter or cleric all of a sudden.  <p><center>Arathena Dracheseele<br>
51st Reaverette of Innoruuk, <br>
Quorum Angelus<br>
Look Mommy, I can nuke too!
<br> 
<Img src="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/120/59/31205922.jpg"><p>
<img src="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/868/62/28686215.jpg" ></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrimhoff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brimhoff</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Say something damn it!</span><br>  Posts: 274<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/21/01 11:40:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How much does taunt &quot;taunt&quot; ?</span><hr size=1> Taunt will bump you to the top of the hate list if succesful but it wont keep you there if you do nothing, nor does it neccasarilly mean that you will be the mobs next target when it swings (in between you taunting and the mobs nesxt swing someone else may get its attention).  As a Paladin Ive found that merely attacking and hitting the taunt key alone doesnt help much to get the aggro I'll have to keep chain stunning as well to get its attention so Im inclined to aggree with those that say the higher you are on the hate list to begin with the more succesful you are likely to be with taunting.   <p>Brimhoff
55th Knight
<Harpers></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utagarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tagarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/30/01 12:19:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How much does taunt &quot;taunt&quot; ?</span><hr size=1> It seems to me that the idea that the hate list in linear is where the problem is.  When a mob changes from its natural (im doing my job) state to its attack (cool, something to kill) state, the mob assigns a number to PC that agroed it.  That number is most likely a formula of faction+damage received+special effect(ie spells that effect them or persons on thier hate chart).  <br>
<br>
Now, when the creature encounters other characters it will do the same for those other characters.  Note, that once a mob is engaged, if someone in the party does nothing to it or others on its hate list, it never adds them.  This is how one can avoid unnessacary faction hits.  I do this alot in SolA with the gnomes so I can keep my ally faction. <br>
<br>
So, its not so much that you are bumping yourself to the top of a list.  You are instead adding to your personal hate with that enemy.  A &quot;Taunt&quot; adds a specific amount of hate to the creature same as stun or mez or whatever.  If your number significantly exceeds all others on its hate list you will receive the next attack.  I say significanlly because even though your number may be a bit greater than others on its chart, the creature also determines if its hate for you is enough to warrent breaking contact with its current target.  (ie your out of normal agro range, how much damage per tick is it taking at is current location, can the mob cast on you without breaking contact, ect) <br>
<br>
I may be wrong, but I dont believe the AI used for the creatures is as simple as a list that you are either on top of or not.<br>
<br>
Tagarth     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwyxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyxx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/14/01 11:50:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How much does taunt &quot;taunt&quot; ?</span><hr size=1> All good advice, and I really don't have much to add, other than the fact that as a ranger I usually cannot keep mobs *off* me; using fast weapons seem to really get a mob's attention...you might not be doing as much damage, but those annoying little stings really hack them off....also two other things I have noticed....having spells resisted seems to put you on the mob's &quot;oh a weakling&quot; list, and they will turn thier attention to the &quot;easy target&quot; albiet momentarily.  Movement hampers ie snare root, etc also really really tick them off, but as mentioned earlier the key is not necisarily to get the mob's attention but then to keep it.  Also a little trick I learned that does the job every time....stop attacking briefly, then re-engage while simulaneously taunting.  I don't know how this works, perhaps you are wiped from the mob's &quot;threat&quot; rating, and reenaging jumps you to the top of the list, but it does work.<br>
